Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.16,0:00:18.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}The dreams embraced by a single life{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.17,0:00:25.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}are boundless beyond even the stars.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.18,0:00:32.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}The dreams that we foster over time{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.18,0:00:40.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}are waiting for the moment\N{\c&He1e1e1&}when we come upon them.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.86,0:00:47.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}The words we exchange\N{\c&He1e1e1&}make our hearts tremble,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.87,0:00:52.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}and a chance meeting\N{\c&He1e1e1&}could change the future.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.21,0:01:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}People, no matter who they are,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}as they pursue their dreams,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.48,0:01:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}have the courage to travel new paths.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.15,0:01:15.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}As we leave behind a living\N{\c&He1e1e1&}testament of our journey,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.49,0:01:26.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}the Galaxy Railways on which\N{\c&He1e1e1&}we travel continue ever on.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.29,0:01:45.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}There once was a spirit that\N{\c&He1e1e1&}wandered through the darkness.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.29,0:01:48.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}This spotless mind,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.23,0:01:52.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}which was plunged down into the\N{\c&He1e1e1&}depths of an implausible darkness...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.97,0:02:05.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}wept because of its purity...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.18,0:02:09.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}continually rejected the light\N{\c&He1e1e1&}because of its purity...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.11,0:02:14.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}"Shrieking in the Darkness, part II"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.99,0:02:19.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Incoming message from Spica Platoon.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}All cars from {\i1}No. 124{\i0} on the Altair Line
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.72,0:02:21.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}have been lost,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}and there are no survivors.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.99,0:02:23.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Incoming message from Sirius Platoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.66,0:02:25.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}All cars from {\i1}No. 811{\i0} on the\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Regulus main line have been lost,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.73,0:02:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}and there are no survivors.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.67,0:02:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}All units, you are authorized\N{\c&He1e1e1&}to warp to Addylos Junction.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.60,0:02:32.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Deliver a situation\N{\c&He1e1e1&}report upon your arrival.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.67,0:02:34.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Thank you for waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.01,0:02:38.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.68,0:02:42.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}There's nothing better than ramen\N{\c&He1e1e1&}when you don't have an appetite.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.01,0:02:43.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I've never heard that.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.02,0:02:48.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You didn't know? And you,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}the son of a restauranteur!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.69,0:02:50.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I humbly accept this meal.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.36,0:02:52.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.97,0:03:05.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}This is good!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.97,0:03:07.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.31,0:03:09.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It tastes kind of like my mom's.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.31,0:03:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}That's terrific! Generally,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}whatever has happened can be undone,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.78,0:03:15.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}so don't be too depressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.65,0:03:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}There are always jobs\N{\c&He1e1e1&}available as shop assistants.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.28,0:03:19.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}If you want, you could go\N{\c&He1e1e1&}back to Tabito, couldn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.65,0:03:22.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I know. You could go help out\N{\c&He1e1e1&}around your mom's place.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.99,0:03:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I've already said my goodbyes to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.32,0:03:29.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What exactly did you go and do at work?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.99,0:03:33.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I didn't "go and do" anything.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}I wasn't able to do anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.67,0:03:38.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}There was nothing I could do...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.67,0:03:41.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I didn't know what to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.02,0:03:54.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}There's nothing we can do here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.35,0:03:59.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}How many people are there\N{\c&He1e1e1&}inside those flames?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.02,0:04:01.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Louis, give a status\N{\c&He1e1e1&}report to Headquarters.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.96,0:04:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}R. Right...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.96,0:04:08.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Galaxy Railways Headquarters,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}this is SDF Sirius Platoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.03,0:04:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}We have arrived at Addylos Junction.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.64,0:04:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Here is our situation report...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.31,0:04:21.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Dammit, is this supposed\N{\c&He1e1e1&}to be some kind of game!?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.22,0:04:31.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I never realized that you were\N{\c&He1e1e1&}a platoon member in the SDF.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.55,0:04:33.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Is it that surprising?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.22,0:04:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yeah, pretty much.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.56,0:04:37.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Everyone says I'm not cut out for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.56,0:04:40.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It's not so much that\N{\c&He1e1e1&}you aren't cut out for it,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.36,0:04:41.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}as it is that you can't\N{\c&He1e1e1&}keep up with it, am I right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.90,0:04:42.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Can't keep up?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.90,0:04:47.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I don't know you that well, but I\N{\c&He1e1e1&}have a feeling that's what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.24,0:04:52.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It's like you've still\N{\c&He1e1e1&}got the heart of a newborn.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.91,0:04:54.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I {\i1}am{\i0} just a kid, you know!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.25,0:05:00.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Stop, would you? Right here is fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.85,0:05:07.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}But you know...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.19,0:05:11.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You know, I don't mind people like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.19,0:05:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Quit, I tell you!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.86,0:05:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Being a watchdog for the\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Galaxy Railways doesn't suit you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.87,0:05:22.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Catch you later.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.21,0:05:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yuuki Manabu, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.88,0:05:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}...utterly unable to speculate\N{\c&He1e1e1&}as to the reason,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.48,0:05:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}as unrest spreads\N{\c&He1e1e1&}throughout the population.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.55,0:05:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}These incidents appear to be\N{\c&He1e1e1&}serial terrorist attacks carried out
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.72,0:05:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}by an organized\N{\c&He1e1e1&}criminal faction in space.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.55,0:05:42.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}However, no one has yet\N{\c&He1e1e1&}claimed responsibility,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.02,0:05:43.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}nor have there been any\N{\c&He1e1e1&}warnings of future strikes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.56,0:05:45.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}The reasons for this reprehensible\N{\c&He1e1e1&}large-scale destruction
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.66,0:05:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}and indiscriminate slaughter\N{\c&He1e1e1&}are as yet unknown.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.90,0:05:51.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}The Galaxy Railways Headquarters has...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.57,0:05:54.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Subatomic particle-dissolving bombs
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.67,0:05:57.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}were first used by the\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Rommellan Liberation Army,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.57,0:05:59.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}who were in control of\N{\c&He1e1e1&}the Aldebaran front lines.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.57,0:06:02.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Those that use specially\N{\c&He1e1e1&}procured Feglinole,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.11,0:06:05.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}which rearranges elemental composition,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}have the most destructive force.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.18,0:06:08.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}A bomb the size of a baby's fist has\N{\c&He1e1e1&}the power to blow away a heavy tank,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.82,0:06:11.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}leaving no trace of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.85,0:06:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Disguised to look like medicine...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.52,0:06:14.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Manabu...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.86,0:06:16.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Manabu...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.52,0:06:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Move forward, even if it hurts.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.19,0:06:20.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Who's there!?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.53,0:06:28.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}This is a news bulletin.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.20,0:06:30.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}This morning, Rachel Aihara,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.54,0:06:33.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}a passenger bound for Greater Magellan\N{\c&He1e1e1&}on Galactic Express No. 323
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.21,0:06:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}and the first victim of a\N{\c&He1e1e1&}series of terrorist incidents,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.51,0:06:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}was successfully resuscitated.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.55,0:06:40.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Thanks to having the\N{\c&He1e1e1&}proper care given to her
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.21,0:06:42.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}by the SDF's Sirius Platoon\N{\c&He1e1e1&}medical sexaroid,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.22,0:06:45.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}as well as the latest in\N{\c&He1e1e1&}resuscitation techniques,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.49,0:06:47.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}which are being independently\N{\c&He1e1e1&}developed at the medical center,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.55,0:06:48.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}the girl managed to escape death...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.84,0:07:08.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Captain!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.51,0:07:13.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}She may have been saved, but I'm\N{\c&He1e1e1&}told she's all alone in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.85,0:07:15.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yuuki...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.85,0:07:16.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.52,0:07:21.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Sometimes, we have to face\N{\c&He1e1e1&}the worst case scenarios.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.19,0:07:24.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}That's something that nobody\N{\c&He1e1e1&}can do anything about.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.86,0:07:29.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Even so, we must do the best\N{\c&He1e1e1&}we can under the circumstances.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.20,0:07:32.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}No matter what those circumstances are.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.87,0:07:36.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Even if your comrades are\N{\c&He1e1e1&}killed before your eyes...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.54,0:07:40.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}we have to endure our sorrows,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}and control our anger,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.71,0:07:43.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}or we cannot serve\N{\c&He1e1e1&}as SDF platoon members.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.88,0:07:46.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}That's something I was\N{\c&He1e1e1&}taught by your father.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.22,0:07:59.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}I never realized that you were\N{\c&He1e1e1&}a platoon member in the SDF.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.89,0:08:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}It's not so much that\N{\c&He1e1e1&}you aren't cut out for it,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.63,0:08:04.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}as it is that you can't\N{\c&He1e1e1&}keep up with it, am I right?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.83,0:08:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}You're not fit to be\N{\c&He1e1e1&}an SDF platoon member{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.87,0:08:09.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}based only on dreams and infatuation.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.17,0:08:11.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}If you think you can get by with\N{\c&He1e1e1&}that utopian attitude of yours,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.94,0:08:14.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}then leave the SDF right now.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.84,0:08:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}It's like you've still\N{\c&He1e1e1&}got the heart of a newborn.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.84,0:08:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}But you know, I don't\N{\c&He1e1e1&}mind people like that.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.18,0:08:24.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Captain!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.18,0:08:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Remember where we are, Yuuki.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.52,0:08:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.52,0:08:30.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Captain, please take me off suspension.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.19,0:08:38.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I don't think I'll change, but no matter\N{\c&He1e1e1&}what happens, I will not stand still.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.20,0:08:41.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Please let me return to duty, I beg you!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.87,0:08:46.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Do as you will. I told you to\N{\c&He1e1e1&}make up your mind for yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.21,0:08:48.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Captain...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.54,0:08:51.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Get back to your room\N{\c&He1e1e1&}and change right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.55,0:08:53.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Once all of the platoons' trains\N{\c&He1e1e1&}have been serviced,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.88,0:08:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}the SDF is moving out in force.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.55,0:08:58.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Don't be late, Yuuki!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.02,0:09:00.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}We're going to do everything\N{\c&He1e1e1&}we can to stop the next bombing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.82,0:09:03.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.49,0:09:04.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}System check!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.49,0:09:06.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}System check, standby.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.49,0:09:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Orbital communications radar\N{\c&He1e1e1&}reading normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.50,0:09:10.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Big One{\i0} moving to launch position.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.50,0:09:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Everyone, I apologize for\N{\c&He1e1e1&}the inconvenience earlier...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.84,0:09:17.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Manabu, hurry and sit down.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.84,0:09:24.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Manabu, look at your monitor.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Every train that has been affected
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.31,0:09:26.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}was attacked within 20 hours\N{\c&He1e1e1&}of leaving Destiny.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.18,0:09:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Engage main circuits.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.52,0:09:30.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Engaged.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.85,0:09:32.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Systems all green!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.52,0:09:36.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Big One{\i0}, move out!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.54,0:09:57.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}If you're serious about\N{\c&He1e1e1&}making a fresh start,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.51,0:10:00.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}then get rid of that\N{\c&He1e1e1&}useless gun of yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.21,0:10:04.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I've been serious from the start.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}I won't cause any more problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.22,0:10:11.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}A large number of trains are now\N{\c&He1e1e1&}departing up through the sky
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.29,0:10:13.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}from Galaxy Railways Headquarters.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.23,0:10:15.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Please be sure to pray for their safety.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.58,0:10:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Picking up the {\i1}Fort Worth{\i0}.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Range, 0.3 spacekilos.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.92,0:10:39.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Bring us alongside them.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.25,0:10:40.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Coming alongside...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.26,0:10:48.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I have explained the hypothetical\N{\c&He1e1e1&}situation to the passengers.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.73,0:10:50.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}There is no danger of panic.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.27,0:11:03.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Maintain speed and raise shields.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Connect the tube.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.24,0:11:06.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Move all passengers to\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Big One{\i0}'s rearward cars.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.56,0:11:20.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}There's nothing on the outside!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.56,0:11:23.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I don't see anything inside, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.90,0:11:32.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yuuki-{\i1}kun{\i0}...?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.92,0:11:51.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Say, Granny...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.26,0:11:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.59,0:11:56.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Your son died in a\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Galaxy Railways-related accident,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.03,0:11:57.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}didn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.26,0:11:59.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.27,0:12:03.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}So why do you work with\N{\c&He1e1e1&}the Galaxy Railways here?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.54,0:12:05.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}That's a good question...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.27,0:12:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Maybe it's because my son\N{\c&He1e1e1&}liked the Galaxy Railways so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.88,0:12:11.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Why are you asking all of a sudden?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.54,0:12:13.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Oh, it's nothing, really.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.55,0:12:22.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'll bet your mother\N{\c&He1e1e1&}must be tickled these days.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.56,0:12:26.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}For having raised such a good boy, I mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.89,0:12:29.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What if you closed early today?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.63,0:12:31.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It looks like the rain is\N{\c&He1e1e1&}just going to get worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.56,0:12:33.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yeah, you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.90,0:12:37.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I just remembered, Granny...\N{\c&He1e1e1&}I have a favor to ask of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.59,0:13:01.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Please show us your identification.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.53,0:13:07.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Halt!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.87,0:13:13.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Aren't you done yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.87,0:13:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}There it is!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.88,0:13:22.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It couldn't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.22,0:13:29.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Rigel Platoon has completed\N{\c&He1e1e1&}bomb disposal on {\i1}No. 576{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.89,0:13:33.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}No. 388{\i0}, bound for Perseus,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}has just passed the Double Clusters.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.56,0:13:35.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Capella Platoon has begun following them.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.90,0:13:38.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Intruder within Headquarters!\N{\c&He1e1e1&}He appears to be armed!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.57,0:13:41.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}All SDF units mobilize!\N{\c&He1e1e1&}All personnel on alert status!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.57,0:13:43.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Shaw-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.91,0:13:48.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Be careful, there's a\N{\c&He1e1e1&}terrorist here somewhere...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.86,0:14:09.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}That was nice work, Manabu.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.53,0:14:13.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}To think that he had disguised\N{\c&He1e1e1&}himself as an ordinary tradesman...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.53,0:14:16.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Hey, what is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.20,0:14:17.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Captain,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.54,0:14:20.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}could I ask you to give\N{\c&He1e1e1&}the order to return?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.54,0:14:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What are you talking about!?\N{\c&He1e1e1&}We've got to handle the next train!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.54,0:14:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Explain your reasons.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.22,0:14:31.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I know the vendor.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.22,0:14:40.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I don't even want to think that he is\N{\c&He1e1e1&}a tool of the terrorists, and yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.89,0:14:41.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Not good enough!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.56,0:14:47.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}He... Shaw said this to me:
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.57,0:14:50.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}"The SDF is the\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Galaxy Railways' lap dog."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.24,0:14:56.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You mean, he has a beef with the SDF...\N{\c&He1e1e1&}no, the whole Galaxy Railways?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.91,0:14:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}If that's the case,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}then he's really after...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.52,0:15:11.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Galaxy Railways Headquarters?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.86,0:15:12.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Captain...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.53,0:15:14.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Captain...!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.19,0:15:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Let's head back!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.86,0:15:18.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It could already be too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.20,0:15:21.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Louis, check the communication\N{\c&He1e1e1&}lines with Headquarters.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.87,0:15:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.54,0:15:25.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What is it, Louis?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.21,0:15:27.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}All channels have been shut down!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.21,0:15:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Contact all platoons! Have them\N{\c&He1e1e1&}coordinate bomb disposal duties!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.55,0:15:33.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Sirius Platoon is heading home!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.88,0:15:34.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}--Roger!\N{\c&He1e1e1&}--Roger!\N{\c&He1e1e1&}--Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.22,0:15:41.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}This is Galaxy Railways Headquarters\N{\c&He1e1e1&}to all SDF units--
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.89,0:15:44.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}As of now, service on\N{\c&He1e1e1&}all lines is being halted.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.89,0:15:48.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}We are grateful for all the loyalty\N{\c&He1e1e1&}with which you have served us daily.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.23,0:15:49.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It is not necessary for you\N{\c&He1e1e1&}to return to Destiny,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.90,0:15:51.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}although this does not\N{\c&He1e1e1&}apply to those of you
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.23,0:15:53.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}who would like to follow the\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Galaxy Railways to its demise.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.67,0:15:54.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}That is all.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.17,0:16:04.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Thank you. That was well done.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.51,0:16:07.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'm the only one who needs\N{\c&He1e1e1&}to remain here, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.18,0:16:10.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You appear to be under\N{\c&He1e1e1&}the wrong impression.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.15,0:16:11.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Anyone that wants to run away can leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.52,0:16:18.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}So, this day has arrived...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.19,0:16:20.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What is your objective?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.19,0:16:24.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I just want to crush the Galaxy Railways!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.53,0:16:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Young man...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.20,0:16:30.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You have come here after all, have you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.21,0:16:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Who are you!?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.21,0:16:38.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Act pretentious with me, will you!?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.51,0:16:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Does that mean you're the big boss\N{\c&He1e1e1&}behind the Galaxy Railways!?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.22,0:16:45.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Please! Please!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.22,0:16:47.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Please!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.22,0:16:52.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Please! Please let me on!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.23,0:16:55.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Those who do not have a pass\N{\c&He1e1e1&}are not allowed to board.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.23,0:16:58.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}If it's about the money, I'll pay\N{\c&He1e1e1&}you back sometime, so please!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.57,0:16:59.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Those are the rules.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.50,0:17:07.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Please! My mom is sick! I need to\N{\c&He1e1e1&}get to her doctor on Heavy Melder!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.18,0:17:10.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.51,0:17:14.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Hold on!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.18,0:17:16.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Let me on board!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.85,0:17:21.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Please!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.19,0:17:23.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Let me on!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.53,0:17:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Who are you!?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.86,0:17:34.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}Shaw, please, don't be here!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.87,0:17:38.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Who are you, with those eyes that\N{\c&He1e1e1&}seem to see through everything!?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.54,0:17:39.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Hold it!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.21,0:17:43.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Shaw!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.21,0:17:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Manabu?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.88,0:17:46.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}There's just one of them?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.89,0:18:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What, you returned to your post?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.50,0:18:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I was sure you had quit.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.50,0:18:08.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Shaw, why are you doing this?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.50,0:18:13.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I have lived my life for this day!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.17,0:18:14.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You what?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.51,0:18:16.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Manabu, unless you'd rather die...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.18,0:18:21.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Why, you dirty bastard...!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.52,0:18:28.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.86,0:18:32.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You stupid bastard!\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Out of the way, rookie!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.86,0:18:34.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yuuki-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.86,0:18:39.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Shaw...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.87,0:18:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Shoot me some more!\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Hurry up and shoot me to death!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.54,0:18:47.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Aim right here!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.21,0:18:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}As you wish!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.55,0:18:55.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Don't shoot! That's an\N{\c&He1e1e1&}old-model atomic battery!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.55,0:18:57.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Hit that, and we'll all be blown away!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.88,0:18:59.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}He's deliberately using\N{\c&He1e1e1&}an antique like that!?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.89,0:19:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}The bomber himself is a bomb?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.16,0:19:03.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Why would he go that far?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.82,0:19:07.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Aren't you going to shoot me?\N{\c&He1e1e1&}If not, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.83,0:19:16.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Aim for his head.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.17,0:19:17.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Shaw, stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.17,0:19:18.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yuuki-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.17,0:19:20.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}--Manabu!\N{\c&He1e1e1&}--Yuuki! Get down!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.51,0:19:23.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Shaw! Get your hands up!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.84,0:19:25.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Manabu...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.18,0:19:26.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Is he...!?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.18,0:19:32.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Get your hands up, Shaw!\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Otherwise... otherwise, I'll.. have to...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.52,0:19:33.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You foolish scumbag...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.85,0:19:36.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Why, Shaw? After what you did for me...?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.19,0:19:38.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Why, Manabu?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.86,0:19:42.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}--Why do you protect the Galaxy Railways?\N{\c&He1e1e1&}--What?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.53,0:19:46.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It was the Galaxy Railways that took the\N{\c&He1e1e1&}lives of your father and older brother,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.97,0:19:48.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.20,0:19:52.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I wanted to save my sick mother.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}I wanted her to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.87,0:19:56.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}All the Galaxy Railways is are\N{\c&He1e1e1&}ironclad rules and train schedules
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.71,0:19:57.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}timed out to the second.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.54,0:19:58.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Shaw...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.54,0:20:01.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}The Galaxy Railways is a\N{\c&He1e1e1&}monster that has lost its heart!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.98,0:20:04.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}We should push its reset button, Manabu!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.89,0:20:10.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}No...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.22,0:20:14.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}No! Whatever your reasons are,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}what you've done here is wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.23,0:20:17.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}The Galaxy Railways is what\N{\c&He1e1e1&}carries people's joys and sorrows,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.96,0:20:20.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}their dreams and their lives!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.57,0:20:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}My father and brother\N{\c&He1e1e1&}died to protect that!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.07,0:20:25.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}That's why I want to protect it as well!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.91,0:20:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I will defend the Galaxy Railways,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}even if it costs me my life!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.91,0:20:33.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}That is your just cause,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}even if it costs you your life, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.25,0:20:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}In that case, you can die,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}together with the Galaxy Railways!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.26,0:20:50.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Let me go!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.94,0:20:59.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Manabu-{\i1}chan{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.21,0:21:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Granny...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.21,0:21:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.88,0:21:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}He said you'd understand\N{\c&He1e1e1&}when you opened it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.55,0:21:11.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}He said he had one last case\N{\c&He1e1e1&}back in the storehouse,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.25,0:21:13.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}and to be mindful of the expiration date.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.22,0:21:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}How am I supposed to drink\N{\c&He1e1e1&}all of this in three days?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.56,0:21:23.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}That spirit was unmistakably pure,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}once upon a time.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.90,0:21:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}For those who love the Galaxy Railways...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.23,0:21:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}...and those who hate it...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.57,0:21:32.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}and everyone else, their journeys\N{\c&He1e1e1&}come together within the light...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.25,0:21:56.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}How many nights have I\N{\c&He1e1e1&}spent alone since then?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.26,0:22:09.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}Constantly having dreams of the hope\N{\c&He1e1e1&}that you are, as I lightly sleep.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.94,0:22:21.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}The smiles and tears that\N{\c&He1e1e1&}you gave to me and me alone{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.95,0:22:28.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}come to mind every time\N{\c&He1e1e1&}I get disheartened,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.29,0:22:33.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}and I set forth again toward the morrow.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.96,0:22:41.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}The joyful light of the galaxy beckons me{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.57,0:22:47.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}to that beloved person within my heart.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.58,0:22:54.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}No matter how far apart we are,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}my memories will never fade.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.25,0:23:04.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}My heart wishes always\N{\c&He1e1e1&}to be at your side.{\i0}
